    "This may result in decreased expenditures on new business capital and R &D. Berestycki et al. (2022) document that climate policy uncertainty is linked with substantial declines in investment in capital-intensive industries, notably in pollutionintensive sectors subject to climate policy changes.",
    "Extensive research have emphasised the urgency of incorporating the physical aspect of climate threats into economic impact studies (Donadelli et al. 2017 (Donadelli et al., 2021;; Kotz et al. 2021; Pindyck 2021; Donadelli et al. 2022; The Macroeconomic Impact of Global and Country-Specific Climate… 1 3 Kotz et al. 2022; Sheng et al. 2022).",
    "These studies demonstrate that climate risks have a negative impact, not only upon labour productivity and capital quality, but also upon R &D expenditures, thereby lowering economic growth.",
